Upstairs also has walk-in closet, laundry and wonderful loft area w gas fireplace. LL has a workshop and storage. Landscaped yard, updated mechanical, central air. Large front patio to enjoy the outdoors and view the lake. Large decks on south side of home. Dream location. Spotless light-filled Linden Hills home just a short walk to LH village and Lake Harriet!

Main level features include a beautiful open-concept kitchen with stainless steel appliances, marble countertops, subway tile backsplash, a large center island and gorgeous flooring throughout. The upper level master suite features his and hers walk-in closets and a private bathroom with large shower, double vanity and soaking tub. Fully finished lower level includes a spacious family room and additional bathroom. You will love the huge fully fenced in backyard with custom paver patio and fire pit - perfect for entertaining! Located in desirable south Minneapolis neighborhood within walking distance to parks, lakes and restaurants and convenient to Hwy-100, I-35W and Downtown Minneapolis. This home truly has it all, inside and out!

All high end finishes from top to bottom. Designed with the owners in mind, 9 foot ceilings, attached garage and open floor concept, to name a few. Entertaining a house full will be nothing short of easy with extra spaces for guest to roam but allowing the host to be apart of the fun. The master bedroom might keep you from leaving the house. His and her's closets and a luxury master bath that screams serenity. Every cabinet was custom built for this home and finishes are cohesive for flow of a well built home. Enough rooms to grow and an office space with a view!

description:
For sale: $169,900. Don't miss this modern and bright condo in the heart of Linden Hills at Lake Harriet. Absolutely fabulous location - just steps away from great restaurants, cafes, the Linden Hills farmer's market and library. 
Open floor plan with foyer, open kitchen/dining and living. Spacious bedroom, with lots of natural light and frieze carpet. Talk about low maintenance - all utilities included and free on-site laundry. Off-street, dedicated parking. 

Pups and kitties welcome. Sorry no Section 8. 6 month lease with opportunity to extend.

description: For sale: $275,000. Check out this stylish walk out rambler in one of the most high demand locations in Minneapolis! This home features vaulted ceilings, an updated kitchen, spacious bedrooms with a private balcony off of the master, and a finished family room in the lower level with a bonus workshop/ storage space. Conveniently located near parks, highways and restaurants. 3D tour is available.
For sale: $450,000. Attention developers and builders! Location! Location! Opportunity to own on prime 49th/50th and France. Great opportunity for future development. Great potential.

For sale: $349,000. Special opportunity to live in great SW Mpls neighborhood only 1.5 blocks from Lake Harriet in a Town Home at an affordable price! Freshly updated, move in condition with great southern exposure for a light & open feeling! Lovely Oak HW floors plus replaced windows and doors for higher energy efficiency. Beautifully updated kitchen with SS appliances, granite counter tops, gorgeous wood floors and enameled cabinetry. Nice-sized dining area off the kitchen. Classic, ceramic tile bathroom with brand new marble vanity & sink. Sliding doors open to a large deck that overlooks the level, fenced-in yard with storage shed. Spacious, finished walkout lower level with beautiful new flooring and large windows opens out to a patio. The lower level can be used as a 3rd bedroom. Convenient 3/4 LL bathroom with a new vanity. Large laundry room with excellent storage. Central air plus an attached garage. Great walkability only 1.5 blocks to trails of Lake Harriet and nearby shops & restaurants!

For sale: $429,900. Safety and health are our top priority. We are available to show this home virtually and the Seller is allowing for individual showings. Located in the Heart of Linden Hills this is a charming starter home!  Pride of ownership with this current homeowner of 36 years creates a wonderful opportunity for anyone who loves Linden Hills and the lake.  Walkability to the lake, shops and restaurants is a bonus.  We have a long list of upgrades that have been completed on this 2  edroom, 2 bath one level living space.  An attached garage is bonus and the extra deep lot allows for expansion.  It is a perfect one level living space.  Call today for details. We can set up showings privately and or set up a virtual tour on your behalf.  This one will not last!

description: For sale: $929,000. Gorgeous newer construction masterpiece tucked away on a quiet street within walking distance of 50th & France! Enjoy high-end upgrades, light & bright open floorplan, spacious kitchen with center island and walk-in pantry, and main level office with walls of windows and beautiful built-ins! The large master suite offers an oversized walk-in closet with custom closet system, and spa-like private bathroom with separate soaker tub & shower! Two guest bedrooms, laundry room and loft area also on the upper level. The lower level features an expansive great room, additional guest bedroom, 3/4 bathroom and flex space currently used as a workout room! Backyard with privacy fence, paver patio and two car garage.  Bring your most discerning buyers! // Contact Listing Agent with questions or to schedule a private showing: Jeffrey Dewing, JDewing@CBBurnet.com or 952.471.2279!

For sale: $449,900. Showings available this weekend with basic precautions; Gorgeous, updated, fresh and sunny home in walkable location awaits! Main floor features living room, two bedrooms, updated bath, updated kitchen and dining room that walks out to deck. Kitchen was very thoughtfully designed, with new flooring, cabinets, lighting, quartz countertops, sink and backsplash! Upper level is large, full height master suite with updated bath, walk-in closet, and a nice office alcove. Lower level includes warm family room with fireplace, game area and play space. New roof in 2019, new furnace in 2018, new main level windows and landscaping, complete list of updates in supplements. If you want a polished home, this is your chance!

For sale: $509,000. Darling tudor in super convenient Linden Hills location - snuggled right in between 44th & France and 50th & France. Pride of ownership shows in numerous improvements: all new Andersen Renewal windows on 2nd floor, new boiler in 2019, upgraded 200 Amp electrical service, upgraded insulation, and brand new appliances. Charming and vintage spaces and finishes, enlarged, center island kitchen has sweet bayed informal dining + breakfast bar seating. Cozy lower level family room and huge 3/4 bathroom. Backyard is an extension of the living space - great, large deck with gazebo and fireplace. Tons of love has been lavished here - see supplement!

description: For sale: $180,000. The perfect mix... an outstanding location and beautiful one level living. This home is located within Linden Hills. Enjoy being able to walk to Lake Harriet, several restaurants, shopping & much more. This home boasts an open floorplan, granite counters, cherry cabinets, stainless appliances, marble & wood laminate flooring & heated underground parking. Quick possession is possible.

For sale: $495,000. Classic two-story in the high demand Linden Hills neighborhood close to the Lakes and popular shops, restaurants and coffee shops. Enjoy the many miles of scenic biking and walking trails of nearby Lake Harriet and Bde Maka Ska (Lake Calhoun). Freshly updated home in move-in condition throughout. Great, fenced-in corner lot with a paver patio and wonderful southern exposure. Beautiful hardwood floors, foyer with open banister staircase, built-in buffet. Gorgeous updated kitchen open to dining room with cherry cabinets, stainless steel appliances, granite counter tops & hardwood floors. Convenient main level half-bath plus back mudroom area. Upper level has three bedrooms and full updated bath with separate tub & shower. Nicely finished spaces in the lower level with an egress window. Classic open front porch and a two-car garage. Perfect, walkable location in one of the most popular neighborhoods in the Twin Cities!

description: For sale: $1,850,000. The Brownstones on France are a maintenance-free, luxury residential community consisting of 20 units. An amazing location (one block South of 50th & France) where you will find shops, restaurants, and all of the modern conveniences an owner would want. This spacious three-level Townhome has exquisite interior finishes throughout.  An open airy floorplan with an abundance of main level living space for entertaining and relaxing. As you take the elevator or stairs to the 2nd level, you will find a beautiful master suite with stunning master bath featuring bright marble countertops and tub surround.  Accompanying the 2nd-floor master is another spacious bedroom with an adorable 3/4 bathroom. Moving to the third floor, you will enjoy another family room with two additional bedrooms and well equipt mini-kitchen and deck. The elevator services from the private two-car garage up to the third floor. Many rooms have been freshly painted and touched up, ready for move-in.

description: For sale: $319,000. Welcome to this sun-filled, South Minneapolis bungalow! Gleaming hardwood floors, a gas-fireplace, spacious living areas perfect for entertaining, & a private family room will certainly catch your eye on the main level. An element of charm is added throughout the home thanks to original woodwork, piano windows, & a built-in buffet that lends a classic feel. The kitchen boasts abundant cabinetry & lots of space to prepare your favorite recipes for friends & family! Cozy up for sunny afternoons spent reading or movie nights in the family room that overlooks the backyard. 3 bedrooms sit on the upper level with the home's full bath. Carpeting on this level is brand new! You will find great storage space throughout. The detached 2-car garage will surely be appreciated during MN winters. This home is right around the corner from Pizzeria Lola and Cafe Vin! Also a quick drive to shops & major highways that bring you to the heart of the city. Don't miss the opportunity to call it yours!

For sale: $1,349,000. A landmark residence in Linden Hills, just steps from Lake Harriet. Built on two lots, including an old growth "forest" that's been thoughtfully encouraged and enhanced. This stunning Queen Anne has been meticulously updated and maintained with respect to its 1910 era construction and architectural beauty. Detailed woodwork, from intricate inlaid hardwood floors, six paneled doors and built-ins, to deep moldings and beamed ceilings. Charming turret rooms and spacious bedrooms. New period-correct kitchen and full bath designed by Otogawa-Anschel in 2012 with in floor-heat. Three porches include the welcoming front porch, a sweet South facing sunroom + 4 season porch on 2nd floor. Wonderful 3rd floor amusement room has its own gas fireplace + 5th BR and an extra turret room. Quality-designed lower level 3/4 bath has heated floor & towel bar, custom cabinetry & glass shower. Too many thoughtful updates and improvements to list - please see supplement!

description: For sale: $1,320,500. For sale: $739,900. Stunning craftsman style remodel/build in the highly sought after Fulton Neighborhood. This home has been completely renovated top to bottom including a second story addition. On the third floor, you will appreciate hand-carved trim, a grand fireplace, and an additional family room.

Walk out to backyard oasis.

description: Recently sold: $337,900. Charming home in the heart of the Armatage neighborhood. With four bedrooms and two full baths this home retains much of its original character with modern upgrades including central air and heat, new carpet upstairs, upgraded kitchen, newer Pella windows, walk-in closets in the upstairs expansion, and a two+ car garage. Original hardwood floors on the main level and a working wood burning fireplace create a cozy space in the winter, and the large deck off the kitchen and mature trees in the yard make a great summer space for relaxing, family time, or entertaining. Conveniently located with major bus-lines on Xerxes, and the express bus stop to downtown is on the corner. Walk along Minnehaha Creek, or to the Armatage playground. Perfect opportunity with plenty of options to expand in a desirable neighborhood.

Walking distance to 50th & France, Minnehaha Creek and several playgrounds, and a short commute to downtown Minneapolis. This beautiful and well-cared for home has a wonderful combination of charm and updating, including built-in cabinets and buffet, tiling and a brick fireplace. The First floor features two bedrooms, a full bath and an enchanting sunroom. The spacious second-floor master suite offers vaulted ceilings, a skylight and a full tile bath. The finished basement provides a family room, study area, half bath and loads of storage. Private fenced backyard features native plantings, plenty of shade, a patio and a two-car garage with new roof and vinyl siding. Updates include: painted exterior (2019), new roof (house and garage, 2016), new furnace and AC (2015), new water heater (2016), new dishwasher (2015) and a new refrigerator (2017). A fabulous home!

description: Recently sold: $362,300. Another great listing offered by Kellen Harmon with Renters Warehouse. This 3 bed, 2 bath, 2 car garage Armatage house is clean and ready for move-in. The main level was recently renovated and the basement is newly finished. There are 2 bedrooms on the main level, a full bath, updated kitchen, and a large family room with a wood-burning fireplace. There is a side entry door that leads to the fully fenced yard (front & back). The backyard has a 10x8 (rough estimate) patio with small garden and there is a 2 car garage with a parking pad large enough for two more vehicles. The upstairs is a 1/2 story with ample room where the 3rd bedroom is located. The basement has a large living room, 3/4 bathroom, laundry room, and storage. Tenants are responsible for all utilities and lawn & snow. $55 App fee, one-time $150 lease admin fee, and a $7 per month processing and reporting fee of rental payments.

Recently sold: $1,550,000. This 2017 Artisan Home Tour gem has 4 bedrooms, 5 baths & a 3-car garage. Combining stone, cedar, steel, floor to ceiling windows & smooth Hardie lap siding, this home's modern finishes are on point. This highly sought after David Charlez Design home is as environmentally sensitive and energy efficient as it is beautiful. It's Energy Star Certified & features non-toxic materials to achieve superior indoor air quality and peace of mind. Striking reclaimed hardwood Elm is underfoot with warm, custom Walnut cabinetry throughout. The open main level living area is oriented toward exquisite views of Minnehaha Creek. From the spacious butler pantry the kitchen flows to the great room, dining room, sunroom, to the tranquil outdoor space. Upstairs boasts 4 bedrooms including 1 en suite and an exceptional master suite w/ breathtaking views, sitting room with 2-sided fireplace, generous closet & full bath. Take the picturesque walking bridge to shopping, dining & entertainment at 50th & France.

Recently sold: $345,000. Immaculate 2 story unit at the Fulton Lofts. Beautifully maintained and updated throughout. All new windows, new dishwasher, dining room light fixtures, refinished hardwood floors, paint, siding, gutters and updated common areas. Open floor plan with lots of natural light and 9' ceilings. Unit features 3 bedrooms on the upper level and private master suite. This is the 2nd largest residential unit within the building. Just a short walk to all the wonderful conveniences that 50th and France has to offer and easy access to parks, trails and Lake Harriet!

description: Recently sold: $481,500. Sunny, classic up/down duplex in the established Fulton neighborhood. description: For sale: $2,495,000. This modern masterpiece features an incredible main floor master suite, a large two-story vaulted great room and kitchen, and incredible site lines which overlook Minnehaha Creek and an exquisite wooded backyard. An abundant amount of wildlife is right out your doorstep, yet this incredible home is still only footsteps away from all the shops and restaurants at 50th and France as well as being just a short 3 minute drive to Southdale Mall and Hwy 62. Built by 9 time Dream Home award recipient Sustainable 9 Design + Build, this eco-friendly home will be custom crafted with high-end materials in their signature "Minnesota Modern" architectural style. Or you can choose to start from scratch and design new! This home will also feature two wet bars, a game room, a massive outdoor patio, two spacious decks, a metal roof and a "green roof" area, 3 fireplaces, a huge kitchen with a massive walk-in pantry, a main floor laundry and huge mudroom area, and multiple media room or office locations.

Recently sold: $924,900. So much house at such a great price, only $226 per sq ft for nearly new construction! All the usual goodies plus high ceilings, main floor office, big back yard, fantastic storage and great finishes throughout in a nice East Edina neighborhood! Don't wait!

description:
Recently sold: $195,000. Live in the heart of Linden Hills neighborhood in South West Minneapolis. Only 1.5 blocks to Lake Harriet in updated 2 BR 1.5 Bath condo. Adjacent blocks have shops, bakery, restaurants, churches, parks, tennis courts and more. Enjoy all that Lake Harriet and Linden Hills have to offer! Updated condo is on 1st floor of secure building and has lots of natural light, lots of storage space and has recently been renovated. Hard wood floors and carpet provide the perfect mix of old world charm and comfort. Updated galley style kitchen includes new appliances, cherry cabinets and granite counter tops. Two nice size bedrooms. Master bedroom has attached bathroom and large walk in closet. 2nd bedroom also has large closet. On premise party room and laundry room with washers and dryers. LEASE TERMS: 6 month lease. Rent includes internet, cable tv service, heat, water, garbage, snow removal and lawn care. Tenant only pays electric. Additional monthly fee for small dog or cat. Rental rate is based on ACH automatic payment. Security Deposit is 1 month's rent. Parking spot is $75 month. 1st month rent and security deposit due at lease signing. This property does not qualify for section 8. Tenants and guests must follow association rules and guidelines. RENTAL SCREENING GUIDELINES: Background and credit checks are conducted on each adult ($45 fee). Credit score, monthly income, eviction history and criminal background are used as factors when qualifying tenants.

For utilities, tenant only pays electric. Heat, internet, cable TV, snow removal, outside maintenance include in rent. 12 month lease. 6 month lease available at higher monthly rent.

description: Recently sold: $349,000. This stunning one and a half story home is on a large lot in a hot neighborhood! Gorgeous hardwood floors, wood windows, natural woodwork are just a few of the highlights throughout this well-maintained home. Enjoy gatherings in the generously-sized living/dining area graced by a fireplace with plenty of natural sunlight. Track lighting in kitchen with stainless steel appliances. Other special features include a spacious family room, plenty of storage space, Huge upstairs office with cozy built-in window seating near master bedroom. Recessed lighting, glass block windows, basketball hoop and large deck for entertaining. Take in the sunny days or the breeze of summer nights relaxing on this lovely three season front porch with swing. Situated in a friendly neighborhood near Lake Harriet with great shops and parks! This home has plenty of character and charm sure to go fast!

Recently sold: $385,300. Welcome to this 1920 Craftsman Cottage! Light floods into each room through energy efficient windows. Tons of original woodwork and trim including a beautiful buffet and glass enclosed bookcases that flank the dining room. Hardwood floors throughout on both levels. Lovely original kitchen nook! Upstairs bedroom and bonus room easily accommodate a nursery, library, office, or guest quarters. Living room, dining room, and sun room all connect for open concept entertaining. Big yard and brick patio with pergola offer the perfect spots for dining, gardening, and recreation. Roof new in 2017 with LeafGuard gutters. Situated blocks from 50th Street shops and businesses.

description:
Recently sold: $1,065,000. This 2 bedroom home is located close to Crosstown and bus stops for easy transportation. It features hardwood on the upper level and all appliances (oven/stove, microwave, large fridge, sink w/disposer, dishwasher and full sized washer & dryer). The large 2-car garage is detached and buts up to an alley with additional off street parking possible next to the garage for an additional 2-4 cars, depending on size. Lower level features a large open rec room and a separate den/office area plus additional storage space in utility room or laundry room.
Tenant is responsible for snow/lawn care: a mower with gas, gas can & oil plus snow shovel are available for use (in the garage).

description:
Recently sold: $575,000. Classic 1920's Linden Hills charmer with surprisingly spacious and updated interior.  This 1.75 story tudor-style bungalow has been well-cared for, with original period tile in entry and in front of fireplace. Lots of natural light, craftsman- and cottage-style details. White enameled woodwork including coved crown moldings. Beautiful light fixtures. Refinished oak floors throughout main level. Remodeled kitchen with in-floor heated ceramic tile, Silestone quartz countertops, new kitchen island, new stainless steel appliances, great cabinet space, garden window, pantry, and coffee bar.
Main floor bath has original pedestal sink and tile floor, new shower and glass block window, new hardware. 
Second floor features huge master suite with separate office/nursery, full bath, sitting room, skylight, gas fireplace, lots of built-in storage. 
Hockey/game room in basement, great storage, updated wiring, newer furnace and water heater. 
Stone-coated steel shake-style roof with 50-year guarantee.
Huge deck off kitchen is great for entertaining.
Highly desirable neighborhood, close to lakes, Linden Hills (Edina, Uptown) shopping and restaurant district, bus lines, great parks, nationally-ranked schools, boating, biking, running, free summer concerts at Lake Harriet . . . 

Neighborhood Description

Linden Hills, in southwest Minneapolis, is one of the city's most desirable places to live, surrounded by Lakes Calhoun and Harriet, close to walking paths and bike trails, Minnehaha Creek, kid-friendly parks, bus lines, nationally-ranked schools, varied architecture, large trees, public gardens, good restaurants, quaint shopping districts (50th & Xerxes, 50th & France, 50th & Penn, Linden Hills, Uptown), and people who take pride in their homes and get involved in neighborhood activities.

description:
Recently sold: $185,500. No Realtor Solicitations Please.  
Live in the heart of the charming Linden Hills neighborhood in a beautiful 1-bed, 1-bath condo on the second floor one block from Lake Harriet. This unit features an updated kitchen and bath, lots of natural light, updated elfa® closets, new carpet in the bedroom, wine cooler, stainless steel appliances, freshly painted walls and other amenities in 800 square feet.

This condo is great for: 
-anyone who loves the lakes/city living,
-anyone who has an active lifestyle (biking and walking paths are one block away at Lake Harriet)
-a couple who commutes downtown, 
-a pied-a-terre for an out-of-town resident, or a  
-Minneapolis base for a snowbird. 
This unit sits in a quiet building that is a good mix of owners and rentals, with a very well run association. 
This property is offered for sale by owner at a special pre-MLS price of $189,500. Purchase price assumes buyer does not use an agent. 
For a private showing, please email the owner by filling out the short form to the right or call. 

Condo Features
- 1 bedroom
- 1 bathroom
- 1 assigned parking space in the underground heated garage
- Rooftop deck with views of Lake Harriet and July 4 fireworks from every angle
- Spacious living room
- Updated kitchen with granite countertops, maple cabinets and stainless steel appliances
- Hardwood floors
- All new windows installed January 2016
- In-unit air conditioning
- Additional storage unit in building basement
- In-building laundry (coin operated)
- Secure building 
- possible additional enclosed garage space to lease in neighboring building

Neighborhood amenities include:
- 10 minutes from Uptown; 15 minutes from downtown; 1 block from Lake Harriet, with walk/run/bike paths, beach, paddle boats, canoes, free concerts/movies at band shell; 1/2 block from bus stop with bus routes to downtown and U of M
- Two doors down from Sebastian Joe's ice cream, Great Harvest Bread Co., Dunn Bros., Tilia, Linden Hills Library, Wild Rumpus, Upton 43, Harriet Brasserie, hardware store
Monthly association dues: $305
Utilities: Association pays water, garbage, recycling and heat; Owner pays cable/internet and electric.

Unit can also make a profitable investment property. The association is very friendly toward rentals.

Recently sold: $515,000. Absolutely charming Tudor home, located in the popular Fulton neighborhood of Southwest Minneapolis.
Picturesque setting with gorgeous views overlooking woods, with seasonal views of Minnehaha Creek.
Beautiful details and old-world charm including lovely hardwood floors and natural woodwork.
Spacious and open floor plan with a nice-sized living room featuring a striking brick fireplace, crown molding and built-in bookshelves.
The formal dining room has two lovely built-in corner hutches and a gorgeous chandelier. The room provides excellent space for entertaining or for family dining.
Kitchen highlights include ceramic tile flooring, a convenient granite eating bar for informal dining and stainless steel appliances.
Bright and cheerful sunroom has newer windows and sliding glass doors that open to the deck.
The large deck, completely rebuilt in 2010, provides a great space for entertaining or just relaxing and enjoying the gorgeous views of the Creek and woods.
Excellent floor plan with all three bedrooms and a full bathroom in the upper level.
The bathroom has lovely stone flooring and a convenient built-in ?make up? table.
Large walk-up attic with high ceilings offers great storage or potential for future expansion.
Great additional living space in the newly carpeted lower level amusement room.
